(Translated by Google) We camped on the Children's Day holiday, we already imagined it would be full. But not so full...
The place was completely packed! There was a promotion on Day Use, which only increased the demand for the beautiful Camping Chap√©u de Sol!
Despite the huge number of people, the format and distribution of the campsite accommodates so many people. The chalets are well spread out and there are 4 tent areas, all quite large and equipped with toilet sets, and quite far apart from each other. So far away that we only saw two of them when we took a drive before leaving.
The place has 3 swimming pools, playground, games room, courts, sauna, paintball, a replica of an indigenous village and other attractions. Honestly, I don't think we could see everything, so I must be forgetting some things and others are not worth commenting on, like the bocce court, which is well detonated.
And they are still expanding! Soon they will have a fishing lake and another pool that will be beautiful!
The service was super attentive and helpful, we saw people cleaning the camping bathroom at night and the team hired to cheer up the children was great. The downside we found was the restaurant and the system used. As I said, the camping is huge and well distributed, you can hardly have an idea of ‚Äã‚Äãhow many people are inside. Until you want to eat or drink something! At mealtimes the only restaurant is quite full and the queue lasts for a long time! There's no point in arriving early, before they release the only serving line, there's already a considerable queue. What prevents the occurrence of wild west scenes is the very family atmosphere and the quality of the food, in the end everyone left satisfied.
I hope that on big holidays they prioritize guests over Day Use, or otherwise, to avoid overcrowding like Children's Day.

(Translated by Google) The place is paradisiacal. As a beach lover, I wouldn't trade the beach for a pool, after visiting the campsite, I would certainly trade the beach for a trip to it. I spent a weekend, checking in at 7pm on Friday and leaving at 5pm on Sunday. I stayed in a simple wooden chalet. It's really simple, for those who go to enjoy and have fun, it's enough to take a shower and sleep. I recommend taking repellent and cockroach poison as we found 2 in the chalet. The barbecue is precarious, the night we had a barbecue it rained and as there is no cover it was almost impossible to have a barbecue, but thank God the rain stopped after an average of 1h30m and it was possible to do it quickly, but the lighting is horrible. I found it strange because I stayed in chalet 30 and the surrounding chalets were all covered, including a table to support things, something ours didn't have. The single mattresses are good, the double mattress is very soft. In the mazanino you have to walk bent over, as it cannot stand upright, ideal for children, adults will struggle even to climb the stairs. I felt that the chalets are quite abandoned, there is no maintenance, there are a lot of cobwebs, but as I said, if you are going to use them for bathing and sleeping, you can deal with it. The food is exceptional, one of the best I've ever eaten in my entire life. Breakfast and lunch are included in the package, lunch drinks are separate but not expensive. We had a total of 7 sparkling waters and a Juice del Valle and it cost 25 reais. The shower burned out and quickly after contacting reception, they fixed it even though it was 9pm at night. It has 6 swimming pools, one of which is heated, meaning that even if it's cloudy or raining you won't miss your trip. In addition, there are other activities, such as a games room, rappelling, sauna, sport fishing, Indian house, playgrounds, among others. The swimming pools have a kind of "step" to sit in the water. The only complaint I have is that the contact via WhatsApp is horrible, I sent a message several times trying to rent it and they didn't even see it until today. I had to take my mother's cell phone to try to contact her and it worked. But since it was my birthday present for her, I had to stop surprising her. comment:
(Translated by Google) I don't come with the intention of harming the place, but I come to vent with great regret. As a regular customer, many managers' attitudes are generally frustrating. I realize that they really don't care about their customers, while lining their pockets is all that matters. I always camp with a tent that costs only 55 reais a day, so far so good, but I have a disabled uncle who helps himself with a wheelchair and a walker, he can't get in and out of a tent. We wanted to take him to have some fun. However, I call to find out if they can provide me with a more affordable chalet, one that is WITHOUT breakfast and lunch included and only one night, but they are not flexible at all when it comes to making an exception for a person with a disability. They only offer a chalet or inn package with breakfast and lunch included from Friday to Sunday for 590 reais, stay unreal. just for something that could be a fairer value just so he can sleep in the establishment with us. This is clearly NOT caring about the customer. They lost a client who was a big fan of the place and I even introduced the place to many different people. Reflect...
